ce:section.ce:para:
The surface chemical compositions and chemical states of the elements of 3-NCQDs/Ag3PO4 composite were analyzed by XPS (Fig. 2
                        ). Fig.2a represents the typical full survey XPS spectrum of as-prepared sample, which suggests the as-synthesized sample is composed of Ag, P, O, C and N elements without the other elements. In Fig.2b, the two peaks in the spectra of Ag3PO4 appearing at 374.08eV and 368.05eV can be ascribed to the binding energies of Ag 3d3/2and Ag 3d5/2, meaning that the Ag element exists in the chemical state of Ag+ 
                        [31,32]. The C 1s orbit illustrates in Fig.2d can be fitted by five peaks. As shown, the five peaks are located at 284.6eV, 284.8eV, 285.7eV, 286.4eV and 288.1eV, which are attributed to CC, CO, CN, CO and OCO, respectively [26,33]. The high-resolution O 1s spectrum is shown in Fig.2e. The broad and strong peak can be divided into five peaks and an AgO characteristic peak appears at 530.5eV, and the other high resolution O 1s peaks respectively center at 531.2, 532.0, 532.6 and 533.3eV, which are assigned to CO, OH, COC and OCO bonds [34]. Both the C 1s and O 1s spectra further indicate the existence of CO and OCO bonds in 3-NCQDs/Ag3PO4 composites. In the Fig.2f, the peaks at 395.7, 399.6 and 400.3eV for N 1s spectrum are assigned to the CN, NO and NH bonds [28,35], which reveal that the composite material surface has the rich functional groups containing nitrogen. The XPS analysis indicates the NCQDs have been modified on the Ag3PO4 materials and intimate integration has been achieved.
